title: For Sale:  Kel-Tec P11 9mm Pistol
postcontent:
My Kel-Tec 9mm pistol is the most perfect concealed carry gun I have ever owned.  I must be crazy for selling it.  It would pass for brand new in the box, but I have carried it and fired it, although it's still in like-new condition inside and out.   I do have the box it came in, as well as two extra magazines, one with the extended finger grip and one flush bottom magazine.  Each magazine holds 10 rounds, plus one round in the gun.

I invested in a Kel-Tec trigger shoe to make the trigger wider, and best of all, a proper Ross cowhide holster that rides high on the belt and tucks in close.

The P-11 is a semi-automatic, locked-breech, double-action-only pistol, chambered for the 9mm Luger cartridge. Ten round and optional twelve round magazines available. The Kel- Tec P-11 is compact and lightweight, thanks to its locked breech. Its ergonometry and practical accuracy are comparable to much larger guns. The P-11 is especially well-suited for plain-clothes police officers, security personnel, or as a secondary weapon for military service members. 

The P-11 has six main component groups: barrel, slide, frame, firing mechanism, grip, and magazine. The barrel is made of SAE 4140 Ordnance steel heat treated to 47 HRC. The slide is also 4140 steel, and contains the firing pin and the extractor. The rectangular frame is machined from solid 7075-T6 aluminum and houses the firing mechanism. The trigger connects via a transfer bar to the hammer and operates in Double Action Only. The hammer is driven by a novel free-floating extension spring. The light weight firing pin transmits the energy of the hammer to ignite the primer. The functioning of the mechanism surpasses all applicable SAAMI safety standards. The grip is made of the ultra high impact polymer DuPont ST-8018. The grip also forms the magazine well and the trigger guard. 

This would be a perfect pistol for personal, home or automobile security use.  How about giving this as an awesome Christmas gift for somebody special. Contact me so we can meet and let you inspect this Kel-Tec P11. I know you won't be disappointed. The price is $275 cash only, and you must show me your Oklahoma Driver's license.

title: For Sale:  Colt LE901-16S 901 .308 Carbine w/ Conversion Kit
postcontent:
At first glance you would think that the Colt 901 is just a .308 Win./7.62 NATO version of a standard AR-15, much like any other .308 AR out there, but it is a lot more than that. The Colt LE901-16S is a “Modular Carbine,” which means it can be adapted to any AR-15 platform upper. This isn’t a new concept, because there are of course a whole bunch of different caliber uppers for ARs. The difference is in all the other ones, they have adapted a standard size AR magazine to boutique calibers and cartridge designs. The Colt 901 is different. It can be adapted from .308/7.62, using standard P-Mags, to .223/5.56, using standard AR mags, and back again, in literally seconds. The design uses one proprietary part, and you have to swap out the recoil system. It is that simple, and it works fantastic.
Exceptional accuracy is assured by its full floated, 16.1” chrome lined barrel and one-piece monolithic upper receiver, suitable for mounting your optic of choice. The fact that most of the operating controls are ambidextrous, including the magazine release and bolt catch makes for versatility and ease of use.

title: For Sale:  Hk G36 conversion from a SL8-6
postcontent:
Selling my Heckler and Koch G36 converted from a SL8-6. It was a TN lower conversion with the bolt and piston changed to US made parts to make it 922r compliant. Tbostic from HKPRO did the magwell conversion and swapped the TN stock for a replica KV stock. I like how it looks but the kv does not lock as tight to it and was eventually going to replace it with a g36c stock with riser. Tbostic also cut and rethreaded the barrel from 20 to 16 in. I have 1 magpul mag and 2 g36 mags. I also have the extra magwell so you can us ar15 magazines. It requires the removal of the front mag catch which is just punching the pin out if you are so inclined. I added the rails from hkparts and the top rail is from a g36 purchased off a hkpro member. The flash suppressor in the pic is aac brakeout but i will keep that and put a thread protector back on. Gun is unfired in both sl8 and g36 configurations. Its a cool gun and probably increasing in collectibility since they discontinued the SL8. Comes with the original SL8 parts and sl8 10 round mag and promag 20 round mag and sling.
Not really looking for trades and in no hurry to sell. Trade interests would be a MR556 plus cash depending on the MR556 model and condition. No hunting rifles or shotguns. I will not respond to low ball offers. Thanks for your interest.

title: For Sale:  WTS defarbed 2 band Enfield rifle. Civil war! Reenact or rifle
postcontent:
I have up for sale a Defarbed Sergeants model Enfield. 

This rifle started life as a 3-digit serial number, euroarms p1858 Enfield. It has been defarbed into an imported short Enfield sergeants model with brass fittings. 

It features a rear sling screwed into the wood of the stock, correct Birmingham barrel stamps, 1861/Tower on the lockplate, "T Turner" on the toe of the stock, various stamps on parts and inside the lock, riveted nose cap, rack number on the bayonet lug, the wood has been thinned down to period dimensions and the metal correctly blued or case hardened. This is representative of rifles meant for commercial market and deemed as 2nd quality firearms by the British system. Lots of these rifles were bought up for use during the war. 

Expertly Defarbed to replicate one that College Hill arsenal had for sale at one point.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Trijicon Dual Illuminated RMR
postcontent: Up for sale is a dual illuminated Trijicon RMR. It features the 12.9 MOA amber triangle. It uses fiber optics during the day to light the optic, and tritium at night to make it glow. No batteries are needed. I had this mounted on an AR for about a year and used the apex of the triangle as my point of aim. Zeroed the rifle at 36 yards and I was good out to 300m. It comes with the following bases/mounts. Trijicon RM33: this base is great for AKs and shotguns. It is a little too low to use on a flat top AR receiver. Yankee Hill Extended Riser: you can use this one in conjunction with the RM33. This brings the height of the site up enough to co-witness iron sights. This also extends the optic past the upper receiver and over the handguard, giving you a better sight picture. Daniel Defense offset mount: this one can also be used with the RM33. This mount is useful if you're trying to run the RMR at 1 o'clock with a scope. Everything that you get is pictured above. Price is firm, at this point I'm basically giving the mounts away.
